comments.body:
For stable Fedora version, our process is that we only put packages that are bound for actual stable releases.  To me, this is what upstream is for.   We really want to avoid bug reporting on unreleased versions, though as a user, I can completely understand the desire.

We also have a COPR repo building from upstream -> https://copr.fedorainfracloud.org/coprs/baude/Upstream_CRIO_Family/  Each commit upstream gets built

@rhatdan @mheon what do you think?
